 1032
Your Honor,

I stand before you today, pleading guilty to the charge of careless driving. I deeply regret my actions on that day and acknowledge the potential harm I could have caused to myself and others on the road. 

In the midst of rushing to pick up my family members from the airport, I allowed my impatience to override my better judgment. I was driving aggressively and at a speed above the permitted limit. Moreover, I made the irresponsible decision to answer a text message from my cousin while behind the wheel. It is with great remorse that I admit my actions resulted in a collision with a guardrail.

Fortunately, I am thankful to report that no one else was injured due to my carelessness. I am fully aware of the gravity of the situation and the potential consequences that could have arisen from my reckless behavior. 

I wish to address the court regarding my character and contributions to society. I am 37 years old and have maintained a clean record until this unfortunate incident. Additionally, I regularly contribute to the British Heart Foundation, recognizing the importance of supporting organizations that strive to improve the well-being of others. 

Your Honor, I acknowledge that my guilty plea on this offense itself carries weight as a mitigating factor. I am sincerely remorseful for my actions and the potential harm that could have resulted from them. I understand the importance of adhering to traffic laws and ensuring the safety of not only myself but also those around me. 

I humbly request the court's leniency in considering these mitigating factors before passing judgment. I assure the court that I have learned my lesson and am committed to making amends for my actions. I offer my sincerest apologies to the court and the community for the disruption and potential danger I caused on that day.

Thank you for allowing me the opportunity to address the court.

Respectfully,

Charlotte Porter

